<div class="forum-post-template-container">
<div class="forum-post-template-title">Straight Talk</div>
<div class="forum-post-template-author-date">
<span class="forum-post-template-author-only">Carla Sherman &nbsp; &nbsp;</span> 
<span class="forum-post-template-date-only"><!--1493771874-->Tuesday, May 2, 2017 at 17:37</span> 
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-author-date" -->
<div class="forum-post-template-post">
<p><span class="forum-post-bold">What we have done so far </span></p><p>About eighteen years ago, while working as spiritual teachers of self-inquiry, Carla and I were taken by the idea that all human psychological misery might have a single cause and a single cure.</p><p>Over time, we came to see that there actually is but one true cause for all human psychological misery; it is the fear of life itself that strikes most of us in the pain and confusion of birth. And that fear creates a context of nonspecific, unconscious fearfulness in the heart of the mind.</p><p>That hidden infection of fear, working silently in the background of the mind from the moment of birth, is the true cause of all human-on-human aggression, and all self-destructive actions and behaviors. All war and all aggression against self and others is caused solely by the terrible burden of the fear of life itself.</p><p>Fear is the one true cause of human psychological misery.</p><p><span class="forum-post-bold">The cure</span></p><p>The simple cure for this disease is to move the beam of your attention inward seeking a taste of the simplicity and ease of being that is your actual nature. Just one look with your mind's eye at your actual, uncontaminated self plucks the thorn of false fear from your mind once and for all.</p><p>If you have already done the act of looking at yourself in the manner we recommend, there's a good chance that you have already seen enough to fully understand the enormity of what we have found here together.</p><p>And if you have not yet done the act, please do so now, before reading any further. Clear and easy instructions on our website will show you how to do it and, if you go to our new testimonials page, you will see for yourself, through reports we receive from people all over the world, the power of this work to bring sanity and ease to troubled minds.</p><p><span class="forum-post-bold">What we want to do</span></p><p>We are writing to you now to ask you to help us bring Just One Look to a worldwide audience as quickly as possible. God knows we need it.</p><p>There is no denying it: the world is on fire. And if you have had any experience with Just One Look's power to free the human mind, you must know by now that this simple movement of attention inward brings a true end to all fear-based beliefs and actions, and infuses courage and self-reliance into minds that were previously terrorized and driven to lash out against other human beings.</p><p>We see clearly the danger that confronts us in these times, but we also see how little it would take, with today's technology, to bring Just One Look to a wide enough audience to snuff out the fear and violence in all of us, once and for all. Sanity is contagious.</p><p><span class="forum-post-bold">What you can do</span></p><p>We know what to do, but we have no money at all beyond the donations we receive which, for quite a while now, have not been enough even to pay the foundation's monthly bills. We always end up short.</p><p>Carla and I can barely pay the rent every month on the house that shelters us and the office of The River Ganga Foundation, the non-profit organization we operate to serve Just One Look.</p><p>We are poor but, having freed ourselves of the fear of life, we are obligated to work tirelessly to bring this gift to the entire human world, using every resource available to us"”until the hubs rub.</p><p>If you know that you are free of fear and on the road to sanity, you must be able to see the importance of shouldering some of the load of bringing this gift to all human beings with us. The more shoulders, the lighter the load.</p><p>Help us today with a donation or a monthly pledge. Without your help, we will not be able to continue for much longer.</p><p>It would be a shame to miss this opportunity to serve our fellow human beings who are crying out for help everywhere.</p><p>Please make a donation today. Time is ticking.</p><p><a href="https://www.paypal.com%5C/cgi-bin%5C/webscr?cmd=_s-xclick&hosted_button_id=JMTUPKF2S696U">Donate with PayPal.</a></p><p><a href="https://www.riverganga.org/Support/category.php?category_id=55">Donate in our secure web store.</a></p><p>"In this world, where fear and anxiety seem to be active at every level"”from the relationship to oneself, as well as to the world, John and Carla have worked tirelessly, often at the edge of going broke (really), to bring their simple but profound message to as many people as possible. Personally, after searching for peace and happiness for many decades, they showed me a door to finding the peace and happiness I already am. The slow change from seeking to finding, and the gratitude for finding this door cannot be expressed in words. If any work deserves support, this is it!" Harvey B., Austria</p>
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-post" -->
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-container" -->







<div class="forum-post-template-container">
<div class="forum-post-template-title"></div>
<div class="forum-post-template-author-date">
<span class="forum-post-template-author-only">roed_ &nbsp; &nbsp;</span> 
<span class="forum-post-template-date-only"><!--1493803868-->Wednesday, May 3, 2017 at 02:31</span> 
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-author-date" -->
<div class="forum-post-template-post">
<div class="forum-post-quote"><p class="forum-post-quoted-name">Carla Sherman</p><p style="margin-top:0;">...</p><p>We know what to do, but we have no money at all beyond the donations we receive which, for quite a while now, have not been enough even to pay the foundation's monthly bills. We always end up short.</p><p>Carla and I can barely pay the rent every month on the house that shelters us and the office of The River Ganga Foundation, the non-profit organization we operate to serve Just One Look.</p></div><p>How we still can be in this situation, that the project's normal running costs are not even covered, is a mystery to me. We're not talking about huge sums here. I hear John sometimes say how many have been cured. I'm like <span class="forum-post-bold">Where are these people and why are people not willing to give you their money!? </span>Pretty much everyone here and elsewhere must understrand by now there isn't a better pocket in world to put it in. It's downright shameful, I don't know what else to call it.</p><p>As a student I got plenty of time but little cash, yet I manage to make a monthly donation. It's not hefty, but it's something. And I will increase the amount. If everybody contributed a little, only a little per person would take us a long way. You know I'm right!</p><p>So if we could all sacrifice only some little convenience in our lives and instead pledge to donate monthly we would stand a much better chance at actually enjoying our future together on this earth. You know, if you need more convincing, you can see it as an investment in humanity, or as your pension insurance... so that we are able to live in peace in the future.</p><p>If anyone has an idea how to answer my question: Why people are not willing to give, I'd love to talk about it. Maybe we can do something about it.</p>
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-post" -->
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-container" -->







<div class="forum-post-template-container">
<div class="forum-post-template-title"></div>
<div class="forum-post-template-author-date">
<span class="forum-post-template-author-only">JaJa83 &nbsp; &nbsp;</span> 
<span class="forum-post-template-date-only"><!--1493844750-->Wednesday, May 3, 2017 at 13:52</span> 
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-author-date" -->
<div class="forum-post-template-post">
<div class="forum-post-quote"><p class="forum-post-quoted-name">roed_</p><p style="margin-top:0;"><span class="forum-post-bold">Where are these people and why are people not willing to give you their money!? </span>.</p></div><p>Well, Roed, I guess the main issue is that most people who land here are psychologically broke; and people who are psychologically broke are, for the most part, also financially broke and that's the whole problem.</p><div class="forum-post-quote"><p class="forum-post-quoted-name">roed_</p><p style="margin-top:0;">Maybe we can do something about it.</p></div><p>Yes, what can we as forum members and people who have done the act of looking, do about it? That's the right question!</p><p>Let us find out what we collectively can do about it. I think this is the right time to start a discussion here: What do you guys think could be done about it.</p><p>I mean we are quite a large number of people here from all over the world, Europe, USA, Asia, Africa all connected through this platform. Can we make use of this connectedness and find a way together to make a contribution to John & Carla, after all that they have been contributing to us? Let's focus on that, I'm sure we will find a way if we do this together. I mean, we have a great starting point, Just take One Look ;) at this map (<a href="https://clustrmaps.com/site/fri?utm_source=widget">https://clustrmaps.com/site/fri?utm_source=widget</a>), we are all over the place.</p><p>So is there a product or service we can develop together, which we can sell and make some money for the foundation. Or can we apply for funding from our corresponding governments. Let's brainstorm...</p><p><span class="forum-post-bold">WHAT IS YOUR IDEA?</span></p>
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-post" -->
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-container" -->







