<p>I'm a part time cleaner ( and aspiring penniless artist ) and I give monthly, too, but perhaps besides the usual reason of basic reluctance with parting with your money is the hesitation of whether this works or not, especially with newcomers? It might take a long time to become apparent that something's changed and it works. But then again, there must be lots of folks who are quite convinced by now, too. Also, fear breeds suspicion and I'm sure a lot of folks feel they've been swindled in the past regarding a cure to their suffering. What do you think?</p><p>Regarding money, what about eBay and Etsy etc? People might have stuff to donate and sell for this cause, if they don't have cash.</p><p>Are there any other Finns here? I think I've spotted a couple of Finnish names here. I'd like to get in touch and hear your story.</p>
