</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-author-date" -->
<div class="forum-post-template-post">
<div class="forum-post-quote"><p class="forum-post-quoted-name">Seppo</p><p style="margin-top:0;">besides the usual reason of basic reluctance with parting with your money is the hesitation of whether this works or not, especially with newcomers? It might take a long time to become apparent that something's changed and it works. But then again, there must be lots of folks who are quite convinced by now, too. Also, fear breeds suspicion and I'm sure a lot of folks feel they've been swindled in the past regarding a cure to their suffering. What do you think?</p></div><p>To me, being involved in the spiritual healing world for quite awhile, this truly sums it up in a nutshell for me. It is unbelievable how many so-called 'spiritual healers' or 'spiritual teachers' claim to have 'the answer', and how people are left off worse because of it. Alarm bells always go off when I here of people charging for healing. The guy I studied with, the most prolific healer I know, never charged anyone for healing. He called it absolute evil to do this. (He tended to speak in absolutes!;-) How can you put a price on getting someone out of a wheelchair, healing someone who is blind or deaf? Of course people donated money, clothes, food, etc to him. It's like John says in his first book to paraphrase: 'If you are doing the right thing and sending the right message out, the universe will support you.' One of my favorite books is called 'The Greatest Manifestation Principle' by Carnelian Sage. There is a quote that comes to mind:</p><p>"When you live your life from the standpoint of being of benefit or service to others or mankind (instead of selfish interests), or operate from the premise of supporting life and all creation, the universe will respond with ways to benefit and support you." - Carnelian Sage</p><p>John and Carla obviously live the first part of this statement very well. It's SO refreshing to see what they're doing in this regard. I can't tell you how rare it is for people to give this way without trying to make a profit off suffering people. And this is the only way it REALLY works!!!  I do wonder though, if having an idea that all human life is going to end and 'we're in big trouble here' is more from a fearful place. Not that John and Carla have the fear, of course, because they are living this experiential understanding. But I wonder if it might not block all the abundance Life could provide. All the best, Lex</p>
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-post" -->
</div><!-- class="forum-post-template-container" -->







